p:
The seroprevalence obtained in this study is in the range of that found in the review by Humphrey and colleagues conducted in urban areas of Middle East and North Africa, with majority of the studies from Red Sea region
9 . Humphrey and colleagues reported a seroprevalence in general population of 25% ranging from 0 to 62% in studies conducted from 1941 to 2015
9 . However, this previous review did not differentiate type of seroprevalence between IgG and IgM. In addition, RNA of DENV was not considered.
